Two doctors commented on Chinese medicine injection and acupuncture anesthesia;
Medical blogger Zhuang Shilihe: Acupuncture anesthesia has a certain analgesic effect, but analgesia and anesthesia are very different. "Those who think that analgesia can be anesthetized can just take two ibuprofen tablets for surgery in the future."
Wuxi Maternal and Child Health Hospital doctor Chen Dashu: Chinese medicine injection is equivalent to an old lady injecting vegetable juice into the vein. Since Chinese medicine injection contains many impurities, it is very easy to cause allergic reactions after injection. https://pbs.twimg.com/media/GiInJZ5acAEmvhP.jpg
